## Interface conventions

{% include 'interface-conventions.md' %}

## What to populate

- `sections` — required sections per interface-conventions.md
  (Invocation, Branches, etc.).
- `files` — `references/*.md` per branch plus example pages.
- `rationale` — selection criteria, branching strategy,
  surface area.

## Output construction

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task design

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task design \
    --set frontmatter.name=demo \
    --set frontmatter.type=interface \
    --set 'frontmatter.description=...' \
    --set 'sections[].heading=Invocation' \
    --set 'sections[-1].outline=...' \
    --set 'sections[].heading=Branches' \
    --set 'sections[-1].outline=...' \
    --set 'files[].path=references/branch-a.md' \
    --set 'files[-1].purpose=...' \
    --set 'files[-1].content_outline=...' \
    --set rationale='Branching strategy and selection criteria...'
```

Syntax: `[]` appends, `[-1]` targets the last appended entry,
`.` nests.
